headline: Should You Buy Disney Stock in May and Hold for 5 Years?
summary: Disney impressed investors last fiscal quarter, increasing revenue across the board and growing the Disney+ subscriber base.  The announced plan to open a new theme park in the Middle East highlights the value of Disney's intellectual property.  Since Walt Disney (NYSE: DIS) reported financial results for its fiscal 2025 second quarter (ended March 29), shares are up a noteworthy 9% (as of May 14).
